			</div>
<p>Force 2025 and Beyond is the Army's strategy to ensure the future joint force can win in a complex world.  Force 2025 improves the force's lethality, mobility, survivability, and expeditionary capabilities.  In accordance with the Army Operating Concept (AOC), Army forces will provide the foundational capabilities required by the joint force.  These foundational capabilities include command and control, along with the ability to project power onto land and from land across the air, maritime, space, and cyberspace domains.</p>
<p>The Army will develop the future force collaboratively with joint commands, sister services, industry, academia, inter-organizational, and multi-national forces.  These efforts will guide changes to Army doctrine, organizations, training, materiel (equipment) development, leadership and education, personnel, and facilities (DOTMLPF).</p>
<p>As the Army focuses on the future, Force 2025 Maneuvers provides the means to evaluate and validate Brigade Combat Team (BCT) expeditionary capabilities in support of joint operations.  The associated wargames, exercises, experiments, evaluations, and other efforts will spur innovation, integrating efforts, and maintaining accountability through the Army Warfighting Challenges (AWFCs).</p>
<div class="blockCallout" id="alignCen">
				<div class="blocktitle" id="cap600">The Future Army's Path</div>
			<div class="blockimage"><asp:HyperLink runat="server"
				NavigateUrl="~/app_Inc-Popup/photo-fullsize.aspx?photo=20150224-01-01-0066-02"
				CssClass="std"
				rel="facebox" ><asp:Image runat="server"
	ImageUrl="~/app_Imgs-Article-Exclusive/20150224-01-01-0066-02b.jpg"
	AlternateText="Force 2025 and Beyond: Preparing to Win in a Complex World"
	CssClass="SiteLandBanner" /><div class="blockenlarge" id="page"><asp:Image runat="server"
